So you only have one autonomous set up through PathPlanner, “line”

Your AutoChooser is set up for once called “New Auto”
autoChooser = AutoBuilder.buildAutoChooser(“New Auto”);

You have to add the other options to your AutoChooser

One thing to try is to not use the AutoChooser and just hard-code the one autonomous

public Command getAutonomousCommand()
{
//this is the only one you run
return new PathPlannerAuto(“line”);
}

But looking at your line autonomous, you have a sequential command that first turns the intake on then waits, I’m not sure that it ever gets to that “wait” because the command to turn the intake on never ends.
